and slide their", "last_comment_created": 1783044408965, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 2, "score_up": 40, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 30, "created": 1783022479000, "id": "2072772627483988414", "video": {"preview": "https://pbs.twimg.com/amplify_video_thumb/2072772552699662336/img/uqLVnkZMI5ZxVU1A.jpg", "mpeg": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2072772552699662336/pl/Y8fmZwBEtApzCl1O.m3u8", "aspectRatio": [360, 329], "heightRatio": 91, "type": "video/mp4", "url": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2072772552699662336/vid/avc1/294x270/qgoIZrcGBR9FHdBc.mp4"}, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1427434033290661891/hLTTZ5lt_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Rothmus \ud83c\udff4", "username": "Rothmus"}, "content": "Back in the day, the KGB would send agents who used \u201ccritical theory\u201d to split every society into victims and oppressors to deliberately stir class against class, race against race, and faith against faith until the fighting created enough chaos to blame the leader, tank his", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 939}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ATBlsteIr", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 27, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8710869, "raw_content": "Justice Thomas in presenting his position in what the 14th intent was regarding birthright citizenship... \r\n\r\n\u201cAs for the evidence in support of my position, it is substantial. \r\n\r\nRepresentative Bingham, the architect of the Fourteenth Amendment, **believed that the Citizenship Clause would not apply to the children of temporary visitors**. \r\n\r\nSenator Trumbull, a principal champion of the Amendment, agreed. \r\n\r\nJacob Howard, who introduced the Citizenship Clause, agreed. \r\n\r\nCongressman after Congressman during the legislative debates agreed. \r\n\r\nCongress in 1870 agreed.\r\n\r\nPresident Grant\u2019s Attorney General agreed. \r\n\r\nPresident Grant\u2019s Attorney General before that agreed. \r\n\r\nThe Supreme Court in 1873 agreed. \r\n\r\nState legislatures agreed. \r\n\r\nExecutive Branch decisionmakers over the course of multiple decades agreed. \r\n\r\nJustice Miller agreed. \r\n\r\nThomas Cooley agreed. \r\n\r\nA battery of other eminent scholars agreed. \r\n\r\nAnd, the great Justice John Marshall Harlan, on three separate occasions, agreed. \r\n\r\nOnce again, \u2018I am quite comfortable in the company I keep,'\u201d Thomas added.\"\r\n\r\n*Clarence Thomas shreds ruling that \u2018devalues\u2019 citizenship in Supreme Court dissent* https://www.coloradopolitics.com/2026/07/01/clarence-thomas-shreds-ruling-that-devalues-citizenship-in-supreme-court-dissent/", "author": "Bullet3250", "created": 1783046013201, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "The PRECEDENT that the Leftist's went AGAINST - in deciding birthright citizenship....", "last_comment_created": 1783046013201, "content": "<p>Justice Thomas in presenting his position in what the 14th intent was regarding birthright citizenship...</p>\n<p>\u201cAs for the evidence in support of my position, it is substantial.</p>\n<p>Representative Bingham, the architect of the Fourteenth Amendment, <strong>believed that the Citizenship Clause would not apply to the children of temporary visitors</strong>.</p>\n<p>Senator Trumbull, a principal champion of the Amendment, agreed.</p>\n<p>Jacob Howard, who introduced the Citizenship Clause, agreed.</p>\n<p>Congressman after Congressman during the legislative debates agreed.</p>\n<p>Congress in 1870 agreed.</p>\n<p>President Grant\u2019s Attorney General agreed.</p>\n<p>President Grant\u2019s Attorney General before that agreed.</p>\n<p>The Supreme Court in 1873 agreed.</p>\n<p>State legislatures agreed.</p>\n<p>Executive Branch decisionmakers over the course of multiple decades agreed.</p>\n<p>Justice Miller agreed.</p>\n<p>Thomas Cooley agreed.</p>\n<p>A battery of other eminent scholars agreed.</p>\n<p>And, the great Justice John Marshall Harlan, on three separate occasions, agreed.</p>\n<p>Once again, \u2018I am quite comfortable in the company I keep,'\u201d Thomas added.&quot;</p>\n<p><em>Clarence Thomas shreds ruling that \u2018devalues\u2019 citizenship in Supreme Court dissent</em> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.coloradopolitics.com/2026/07/01/clarence-thomas-shreds-ruling-that-devalues-citizenship-in-supreme-court-dissent/\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.coloradopolitics.com/2026/07/01/clarence-thomas-shreds-ruling-that-devalues-citizenship-in-supreme-court-dissent/</a></p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 0, "score_up": 27, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ATBlssGj2", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 104, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8710318, "raw_content": "", "author": "Trick", "created": 1783019515298, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "cyberrigger", "is_vide